
[1]hover

   HOV'ER, v.i.

   1. To flap the wings, as a fowl; to hang over or about, fluttering or
   flapping the wings, with short irregular flights.

   Great flights of birds are hovering about the bridge, and settling on
   it.

   2. To hang over or around, with irregular motions.

   A hovering mist came swimming o'er his sight.

   3. To stand in suspense or expectation.

   4. To wander about from place to place in the neighborhood; to move
   back and forth; as an army hovering on our borders; a ship hovering on
   our coast.

             HOV'ER, n. A protection or shelter by hanging over.
